                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName>, Secretary of State,
                        to Mr. <persName type="to">Pierrepont</persName>, district attorney.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-07-07">
                        <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 7, 1870</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <seg type="margin">[133]</seg>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The President has been informed that the Spanish
                    minister is in possession of evidence tending to show that some parties in your
                    district have *been guilty of a violation of the neutrality laws of the United
                    States.</p>
                <p>A portion of this evidence has been laid before me by Mr. Lopez Roberts, in
                    affidavits, of which copies are inclosed, Mr. Roberts has been informed that all
                    witnesses within your reach who may be pointed out to you by him, or by the
                    counsel who may be employed by him, will be examined by you, and that you will
                    thereupon institute such proceedings, civil or criminal, as the case may
                    justify.</p>
                <p>You will, therefore, please act in the spirit of the communication to Mr. Lopez
                    Roberts should occasion require.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, yours, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards Pierrepont</hi>, Esq.,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">United States District Attorney, New York.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
